The award scheme in the advertising industry is set for a comeback this year after a 12-year break. The Association of Practitioners in Advertising Awards says the 2016 fete will be held on November 11. Kenya is home to countless individuals with great creative potential, and these awards are crucial as they aim to recognise and reward excellence, innovation and originality, APA chairman Lenny Nganga said in a statement. The awards gala is set to bring together all industry professionals and stakeholders to celebrate creative ingenuity in the advertising industry. About 15 creative categories will be awarded ranging from TV, radio and print commercials, integrated communications campaign, digital, interactive, experiential, media innovation, sustainable marketing, young creatives award among others.Numerous entries were submitted by the various creative agencies and industry professionals.